# Zeblok GenAI SDK 

The Zeblok SDK allows users to integrate their external MLOps workflows with the AI-MicroCloud platform. Specifically, this new release will add functionality and support for interactions with AI models.

## Components

### Auth

- API Authentication

### Resources

- AI-API
- Client
- Embedding Model
- GPT Model
- Inference Chat

# Interface

<h3> Authentication </h3>

- API Authentication: `APIKeyAuth()`

<h3> Client </h3>

- Create a new client: `Client(api_key)`
- Authenticate API key: `_authenticate_api_key()`
- Add a new model to the client: `_register_model(model_name, model_class)`
- List all models associated with the client: `list_models()`
- Make a request to Zeblok AI MicroCloud: `_request(method, endpoint, params)`

<h3> Models </h3>

- GPT Model: `GPTModel(model_name, client, api_key)`
- Embedding Model: `EmbeddingModel(model_name, client, api_key)`
- Get completions (only for GPTModel): `completions(prompt, max_tokens=50, temperature=0.7, **kwargs)`
- Get chat history (only for GPTModel): `get_chat_history()`

<h3> Inference Chat </h3>

- Create a new inference chat: `InferenceChat(api_key, model_name)`
- Retrieve a response from the AI model: `chat(prompt, max_tokens, temperature)`
- Get history of interactions with the model: `get_chat_history()`

Note that inference chats are not detailed in the usage of the SDK, since their functionality is covered by other modules.

# Usage

Checkout the detailed usage of the SDK at [USAGE.md](USAGE.md).

